'''John Nightingale''' (born December 2, 1928 in [[Saint Paul, Minnesota]]) was an [[United States|American]] [[figure skater]]. He most notably competed in pairs with partner [[Janet Gerhauser]], twice winning the silver medal at the [[United States Figure Skating Championships]] and taking part in the [[1952 Winter Olympic Games]]. He also competed in fours with [[Gerhauser]], [[Marilyn Thomsen]], and [[Marlyn Thomsen]] and won the 1949 [[North American Figure Skating Championships|North American title]].
